<section id="faq" class="pt-14">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1040px] px-6 md:px-16 lg:px-28">
    <h2 class="text-center mb-4 text-2xl md:text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold tracking-wide">FAQ</h2>
    <div class="mt-2 grid gap-3 md:gap-4">
      <details open class="group border-2 border-[var(--ink)] rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:bg-[var(--hover-bg)] transition">
        <summary class="flex items-center gap-3 justify-between py-3 md:py-4 px-4 cursor-pointer text-base md:text-lg font-semibold">
          What is a sharenote?
          <svg class="ml-3 shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="text-[var(--ink-muted)] px-4 pb-4 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed">
          A sharenote is a unit of computational work. Your mining hardware prints it, the network verifies it, and you own it. Think of it like a banknote — except instead of paper and ink, it is made of energy and math.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group border-2 border-[var(--ink)] rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:bg-[var(--hover-bg)] transition">
        <summary class="flex items-center gap-3 justify-between py-3 md:py-4 px-4 cursor-pointer text-base md:text-lg font-semibold">
          Is this a new coin, token, or NFT?
          <svg class="ml-3 shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="text-[var(--ink-muted)] px-4 pb-4 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed">
          No. A sharenote is not a coin, not a token, and not an NFT. It is a proof-of-work note — a record that real energy was spent. You do not trade it on an exchange. You spend it to prove your work is real.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group border-2 border-[var(--ink)] rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:bg-[var(--hover-bg)] transition">
        <summary class="flex items-center gap-3 justify-between py-3 md:py-4 px-4 cursor-pointer text-base md:text-lg font-semibold">
          What can I do with sharenotes?
          <svg class="ml-3 shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="text-[var(--ink-muted)] px-4 pb-4 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed">
          Anywhere someone needs proof that real work was done. Sort feeds by energy spent instead of likes. Weight votes so bots cannot flood them for free. Gate AI agent requests behind a note so every call costs real computation. Audit your mining payouts with records anyone can check.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group border-2 border-[var(--ink)] rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:bg-[var(--hover-bg)] transition">
        <summary class="flex items-center gap-3 justify-between py-3 md:py-4 px-4 cursor-pointer text-base md:text-lg font-semibold">
          What are Work Templates and Sharenote Bills?
          <svg class="ml-3 shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="text-[var(--ink-muted)] px-4 pb-4 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed">
          A <strong>Work Template</strong> is the raw puzzle your hardware solves (e.g., a Bitcoin block template). A <strong>Sharenote Bill</strong> is your target difficulty floor (e.g., <code>20Z00</code>). To print a note, your hardware takes the template and spends energy until it satisfies the Bill's target.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group border-2 border-[var(--ink)] rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:bg-[var(--hover-bg)] transition">
        <summary class="flex items-center gap-3 justify-between py-3 md:py-4 px-4 cursor-pointer text-base md:text-lg font-semibold">
          How do I print a sharenote?
          <svg class="ml-3 shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="text-[var(--ink-muted)] px-4 pb-4 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed">
          Printing requires three things: a <strong>Work Template</strong>, a <strong>Target Sharenote Bill</strong>, and <strong>Energy</strong>. You connect your hardware to a Sharenote-compatible Stratum server, which provides the template and captures the signed result once the target difficulty is met.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group border-2 border-[var(--ink)] rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:bg-[var(--hover-bg)] transition">
        <summary class="flex items-center gap-3 justify-between py-3 md:py-4 px-4 cursor-pointer text-base md:text-lg font-semibold">
          Do I need new hardware or a different pool?
          <svg class="ml-3 shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="text-[var(--ink-muted)] px-4 pb-4 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed">
          No new hardware is required. However, Sharenote requires a protocol-aware Stratum server to manage the printing process. There is an active initiative to integrate Sharenote support directly into standard Stratum implementations so you can continue using your preferred pool. Use the <a href="/the-market/planner-calculator" class="underline">Sharenote Planner</a> to see what your current hardware is capable of.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group border-2 border-[var(--ink)] rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:bg-[var(--hover-bg)] transition">
        <summary class="flex items-center gap-3 justify-between py-3 md:py-4 px-4 cursor-pointer text-base md:text-lg font-semibold">
          Can bots or AI fake sharenotes?
          <svg class="ml-3 shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="text-[var(--ink-muted)] px-4 pb-4 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed">
          A bot can run the computation, but not for free. Printing a note costs real energy. A bot sending a million requests must spend the same energy as a million real users. The math makes mass abuse too expensive to sustain.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group border-2 border-[var(--ink)] rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:bg-[var(--hover-bg)] transition">
        <summary class="flex items-center gap-3 justify-between py-3 md:py-4 px-4 cursor-pointer text-base md:text-lg font-semibold">
          Can anyone verify my sharenotes?
          <svg class="ml-3 shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="text-[var(--ink-muted)] px-4 pb-4 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed">
          Yes. Every printed note is published to the Nostr relay network and signed with your identity. Any miner, app, or third party can read and verify those records at any time — no need to ask a pool for permission.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group border-2 border-[var(--ink)] rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:bg-[var(--hover-bg)] transition">
        <summary class="flex items-center gap-3 justify-between py-3 md:py-4 px-4 cursor-pointer text-base md:text-lg font-semibold">
          What stage is Sharenote in right now?
          <svg class="ml-3 shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="text-[var(--ink-muted)] px-4 pb-4 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed">
          The core specifications (SNIP-00 and SNIP-02) are Stable. The remaining SNIPs are in Draft. Protocol integration is being developed natively for Stratum servers, and builders can integrate today using the <a href="/the-market/vibe-coding" class="underline">Sharenote skill</a> for AI-assisted development.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group border-2 border-[var(--ink)] rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:bg-[var(--hover-bg)] transition">
        <summary class="flex items-center gap-3 justify-between py-3 md:py-4 px-4 cursor-pointer text-base md:text-lg font-semibold">
          What if my pool ignores Sharenote?
          <svg class="ml-3 shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="text-[var(--ink-muted)] px-4 pb-4 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed">
          You can still publish sharenotes on your own to keep a record of your work. Public records make it easier for miners and the community to ask pools to adopt the standard.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group border-2 border-[var(--ink)] rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:bg-[var(--hover-bg)] transition">
        <summary class="flex items-center gap-3 justify-between py-3 md:py-4 px-4 cursor-pointer text-base md:text-lg font-semibold">
          What is Nostr?
          <svg class="ml-3 shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="text-[var(--ink-muted)] px-4 pb-4 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed">
          Nostr is an open network for sending signed messages across independent servers called relays. No one owns it. No relay can change your messages — the signature would break. Sharenote uses Nostr as the public layer where all printed notes are recorded.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group border-2 border-[var(--ink)] rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:bg-[var(--hover-bg)] transition">
        <summary class="flex items-center gap-3 justify-between py-3 md:py-4 px-4 cursor-pointer text-base md:text-lg font-semibold">
          What is the Web of Fun (WoF)?
          <svg class="ml-3 shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="text-[var(--ink-muted)] px-4 pb-4 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed">
          WoF is a movement to give people ownership over what they do online. Instead of letting platforms keep all the value, WoF projects like Sharenote build new ways for users to own and benefit from their work. <a href="https://docs.flokicoin.org/wof" class="underline" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Learn more</a>.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group border-2 border-[var(--ink)] rounded-lg overflow-hidden hover:bg-[var(--hover-bg)] transition">
        <summary class="flex items-center gap-3 justify-between py-3 md:py-4 px-4 cursor-pointer text-base md:text-lg font-semibold">
          Where can I follow updates?
          <svg class="ml-3 shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="text-[var(--ink-muted)] px-4 pb-4 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed">
          Join the WoF Discord in the <a href="https://flokicoin.org/discord" class="underline" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"><code>#sharenote</code></a> channel for live updates. Read the <a href="https://docs.flokicoin.org/wof" class="underline" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">WoF paper</a> for deeper context.
        </div>
      </details>


    </div>
  </div>
</section>

